 <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-extrabold uppercase leading-[0.95] tracking-tight text-charcoal sm:text-4xl">
 The crew that builds Vegas deserves gear that holds up.
 </h2>
 <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 <p>
 General contractors are the backbone of everything we do at Bighorn. If your crew is pouring foundations, framing walls, hanging drywall, or running a multi-site build, you need branded apparel that survives heat, sweat, concrete dust, and the kind of abuse office clothes never see. That means heavyweight 6oz+ tees with plastisol prints that don't crack after one wash, hi-vis safety shirts that meet ANSI Class 2 or Class 3 requirements, and hard hats printed or stickered with your company mark so your crew is identifiable on a shared job site.
 </p>
 <p>
 The challenge most GCs bring us: ordering in waves. You need 50 shirts now for the summer crew, another 30 next month when a superintendent starts, and a one-off hoodie for the owner's nephew who just joined. We solve that with company stores — a private online portal where your team orders approved gear in approved colors with your logo, at your negotiated pricing. No more emails. No more spreadsheets. No more wrong sizes showing up the day before the OSHA walk.
 </p>
 <p>
 Most common orders from GCs: hi-vis tees and long-sleeves, embroidered polos for PMs and estimators, hard hats and hard hat stickers, branded Carhartt-style jackets for winter, company-store reorders, and site-specific safety vests for subs and visitors.
 </p>
