 Moisture-wicking work shirts and branded trucks that win the driveway.
 </h2>
 <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-ash">
 <p>
 Plumbing and HVAC techs spend half their day in attics that hit 140 degrees and the other half under sinks with their elbow in a puddle. Cotton tees aren't going to cut it. We outfit Vegas plumbing and HVAC companies with moisture-wicking performance work shirts that breathe, dry fast, and don't hold the smell of a crawlspace after a long call. Polos and button-downs with your logo embroidered on the chest create an instant "I'm a pro, not a handyman with a truck" first impression when your tech walks up to a homeowner's door.
 </p>
 <p>
 Branded merch matters more in this trade than most. A homeowner who just got an HVAC replacement is going to remember your truck magnet, your branded notepad, your company pen left on their kitchen counter — and they're going to hand your info to the neighbor weeks later when their unit goes out. We build leave-behind promotional kits designed specifically for residential service trades: fridge magnets with your logo and phone number, notepads, branded pens, water bottles for the crew, and embroidered service-tech jackets that look sharp in every driveway visit.
 </p>
 <p>
 Common orders: performance work shirts, embroidered polos, branded service-tech jackets, truck magnets, notepads, pens, water bottles, and seasonal promo giveaways.
 </p>
